OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1777619131
OL,3,CCharles 'raising a dram' after Trump
OL,4,Cvows to lift Scottish whisky tariffs
OL,6,FIn response, a Buckingham Palace
OL,7,Fspokesperson said: "The King has been
OL,8,Finformed of President Trump's warm
OL,9,Fgesture and sends his sincere
OL,10,Fgratitude for a decision that will
OL,11,Fmake an important difference to the
OL,12,FBritish whisky industry and the
OL,13,Flivelihoods it supports.
OL,15,F"His Majesty will be raising a dram to
OL,16,Fthe president's thoughtfulness and
OL,17,Fgenerous hospitality as he departs the
OL,18,FUS after a most enjoyable state visit
OL,19,Ffor both their majesties in this
OL,20,Fspecial anniversary year."
OL,26,@oD@TOUwD@AOU|D@ZO]
